	<text id="ruskin_to_margret_august_15_1867">
	
	    <header>
	        <inventNo>1996L00331</inventNo>
	    </header>
	
	    <body>
	        <div type="text">
	            <pb n="1"/>
	            <opener>
	                <placeName><!-- match letter exactly, delete if unnecessary -->
	                    <rs key="Q1025076" type="place">Keswick.</rs>
	                </placeName>
	                <date when="1867-08-15"><!-- match letter exactly, delete if unnecessary -->
	                    <rs type="date">15th August, 1867</rs>
	                </date>
	                <salute>My dearest <rs key="47637407" type="person">Mother</rs></salute><!-- match letter exactly,
	                delete if
	                unnecessary -->
	            </opener>
	
	            <p id="p1">
	                <s id="s1">I have writen so long a letter to <rs key="76205504" type="person">Joanna</rs>, all of which is for you
	                    also, that I must not write much more to day - only your writing is quite beautiful still - more
	                legible than <rs key="76205504" type="person">Joannas</rs>; (which is legiblest to <hi rend="underline">me</hi> of
	                    lady hands) and I'll be home D.V. on the 24th.</s>
	                <s id="s2">but it is curious that you speak of the <hi
	                            rend="underline">peace</hi> of these hills, for that is indeed the helpfullest thing of
	                    all to me - more than air or exercise - when I come back- you &amp; <rs key="76205504" type="person">Joan</rs> must
	                    go on managing the house between you, for, positively, I won't be <pb n="2"/> bothered with it -
	                    you may open my letters you like, now.</s>
	                <s id="s2">Was'nt <rs key="156994466" type="person">Kingsley</rs>'s nice, about my <rs
							key="73859585" type="person">father</rs>?</s>
	            </p>
	
	            <closer>
	                <salute>For my dearest <rs key="47637407" type="person">Mother</rs>, your most affectionate Son</salute><!-- optional -
	                delete if
	                unnecessary -->
	                <signed><!-- optional - delete if unnecessary -->
	                    <rs key="73859585" type="person">J Ruskin</rs>
	                </signed>
	             </closer>
	
	            <postscript>
	
	            </postscript>
	
